        <div n="818AROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">INSCRIBED TO THE HONOURABLE SERJEANT KITE</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-1"> In your indignation what mercy appears,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-2"> While Jonathan's threatened with loss of his ears;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-3"> For who would not think it a much better choice,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-4"> By your knife to be mangled than racked with your voice.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-5"> If truly you would be revenged on the parson,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-6"> Command his attendance while you act your farce on,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-7"> Instead of your maiming, your shooting, or banging,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-8"> Bid Povey secure him while you are haranguing.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-9"> Had this been your method to torture him, long since,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-818AROGP-line-10"> He had cut his own ears to be deaf to your nonsense.818AROGP   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
